Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,UgwgIcZRP7UhXtbUW414AaABAg,,@jimgreen2080,"Glad you have already said you'll want to see this again. You'll pick up details you missed, and despite knowing what happens will be fully engaged again. The direction, the cinematography--as a wartime production they may not have had a broad landscape canvas to use, but employing light, shadow, super closeups, etc. was brilliant, and the acting is first-rate. BTW, a number of the actors fled the Nazi regime IRL, including Peter ""Ugarte"" Lorre {Jewish) and Conrad Veidt, who played Major Strasser---his wife was Jewish.",2026-05-02T20:31:39Z,2026-05-02T20:31:39Z,2,False,0.0,2026-05-07T02:01:21.481920
