Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgzTQwvxzbqmQPHpizB4AaABAg.AGI_1P2lBjFAGIwOoh7MNZ,UgzTQwvxzbqmQPHpizB4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Wow, Bry, Thank you so much for your very kind words and for subscribing! Please tell your family and friends about us and share our videos. That is what YouTube likes to see and what helps others to find us. We are so grateful for the community we have here! And we loved our time in Morocco. We have a full series that we hope you enjoy. We visited the Sahara Desert and absolutely loved Fes! —Judy
🎥 Morocco Travel Series: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLNT98lWfwdF0_pL4S2LnqlBz2KBX9XMCc",2025-03-30T19:14:45Z,2025-03-30T19:14:45Z,0,True,,2026-05-07T02:02:03.335620
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgygYPhcCHOGoIbCWT14AaABAg.AEsOPMUEOXWAEubupeRRgI,UgygYPhcCHOGoIbCWT14AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,This may be the restaurant that you are referring to in Marrakech. It's where we had breakfast several of the days that we visited (but they also serve other meals as well): https://www.mandalasociety.co/marrakech. —Judy,2025-02-24T02:43:21Z,2025-02-24T02:43:21Z,1,True,,2026-05-07T02:02:03.704019
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgyTkvvc5TMDaXXsxAR4AaABAg.AEro9JX76GPAErpYzBMHFL,UgyTkvvc5TMDaXXsxAR4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Donah, Hmmm. It's tricky. El Badi Palace was pretty cool. We enjoyed it a lot. We have heard from some of our viewers that they really liked the Berber Museum and Majorelle Garden, too. I think it mostly depends on what type of experience you are interested in. I've heard that the garden is one of the most photographed and well-known gardens in Morocco. If you're into fashion, perhaps knowing that the garden was once owned by fashion designer Yves Saint Laurent will tip the scale for you. We are more interested in the deeper history and architecture, which is why we prioritized El Badi Palace. Thanks so much for watching. We have a full series from Morocco that might be interesting to you. We really enjoyed our 40+ days there. We don't think you will go wrong with either site, but they are very different! —Judy
🎥 Morocco Travel Series: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLNT98lWfwdF0_pL4S2LnqlBz2KBX9XMCc",2025-02-23T00:44:51Z,2025-02-23T00:44:51Z,0,True,,2026-05-07T02:02:03.865063
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgxzUobM4Ce3CwnfQRB4AaABAg.AECEE66XrQyAEDOgDxr-mj,UgxzUobM4Ce3CwnfQRB4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Thank you so much for watching! We really think colorful is an accurate way to describe Marrakech! We have a full series from our 40+ days in Morocco if you're interested in watching! —Judy
🎥 Morocco Travel Series: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLNT98lWfwdF0_pL4S2LnqlBz2KBX9XMCc",2025-02-06T22:32:27Z,2025-02-06T22:32:27Z,0,True,,2026-05-07T02:02:04.012622
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgxgTojif_sIweHMebp4AaABAg.AE3KIek4Gb0AEAYfRHrC1D,UgxgTojif_sIweHMebp4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"It's hard for us to not be able to record in certain places, which is why we might opt to skip them. We'd rather put our budget on places we can more easily share with our viewers. Of course, there are times when it's worth it to us, but it's so much easier when they do allow photographs. We use Airbnb quite a bit, but especially in Fes, our riad served us a very hearty breakfast every day and we were really able to save a lot of money not having to chase down an extra meal every day. Our Marrakech location wasn't ideal and although breakfast was cheap, arranging it was a bit confusing, so we only ate in once. Thanks for sharing your experience! —Judy",2025-02-05T20:02:00Z,2025-02-05T20:02:00Z,0,True,,2026-05-07T02:02:04.185237
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgyIVqczQ0iOrKhcO6l4AaABAg.ADlWeBG9LiQADlwbogMWm2,UgyIVqczQ0iOrKhcO6l4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"We don't shop for souvenirs as full-time travelers with no home base, but we are glad to hear you enjoyed this trio of museums. We will have to come back and check them out. We were in the Atlas Mountains, but again we skipped some of the shopping. Thanks for the recommendation about Dar Zite. We have a full series from our 40+ days in Marrakech if you're interested in watching. It's linked below. —Judy
