Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,Ugzw0hdsOOdS-EeaQdx4AaABAg.AD7aowz4S8bAD7dDFFgaiS,Ugzw0hdsOOdS-EeaQdx4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi Ike, We really enjoyed Morocco as well. You should visit Fes on your next trip. We missed Essaouira, but we did do a Sahara Desert tour, which we highly recommend. I'll link our other videos below. We were very fortunate to be able to be in Morocco for over 40 days! —Judy
🎥 Morocco Travel Series: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLNT98lWfwdF0_pL4S2LnqlBz2KBX9XMCc",2025-01-10T20:21:19Z,2025-01-10T20:21:19Z,1,True,,2026-05-07T02:02:05.228787
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,Ugzw0hdsOOdS-EeaQdx4AaABAg.AD7aowz4S8bAECggtk3ww-,Ugzw0hdsOOdS-EeaQdx4AaABAg,@tkozikow,"Did you do a day trip to Essaouira or spend a couple of days there? We have four days in Marrakech next month and our riad highly recommends going there and we are trying to decide if it is worth the trip. From what I have been reading I think we want to go, but appreciate your thoughts.",2025-02-06T15:59:19Z,2025-02-06T15:59:19Z,1,True,,2026-05-07T02:02:05.228802
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,Ugzw0hdsOOdS-EeaQdx4AaABAg.AD7aowz4S8bAIoklAX7TpL,Ugzw0hdsOOdS-EeaQdx4AaABAg,@Kaedehara_egiap,"​@tkozikow hey there! So my best friend and I are heading to Marrakesh for my 30th birthday in July, and I was wondering if you wouldn't mind sharing a bit about your experience and places to go when we're there. We don't mind taking a day trip out of Marrakesh, so anything you can provide would be great!",2025-06-01T06:10:49Z,2025-06-01T06:10:49Z,0,True,,2026-05-07T02:02:05.228806
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,Ugzw0hdsOOdS-EeaQdx4AaABAg.AD7aowz4S8bAIzvTvW8LSe,Ugzw0hdsOOdS-EeaQdx4AaABAg,@tkozikow,"​@Kaedehara_egiap we booked our excursions directly through our riad, and the highlight was a day trip to the Ourika Valley. We had a private driver who arranged for a guide in Setti Fadma to accompany us on a waterfall hike.   There are plenty of small bus/group tours, but I would highly recommend spending the extra money... It was around $175, including the tip, for two people. We stopped at a couple of Berber villages along the way and purchased some pottery and a rug for a fraction of the cost it would be in Marrakech. The guide was around $40 and well worth the money. If you decide to do this, be sure to have decent shoes that are OK for light hiking.

I suggest hiring a guide to explore the souks and key areas inside the medina. You might encounter some sales pitches along the way, but it was an interesting five hours and provided us with ideas for what to explore on our own. You can easily book either of these through a service like Viator, but if you're staying at a decent riad, they should be able to coordinate this for you.

Definitely explore the alleyways and small streets in the medina for the best food and a glimpse of the culture. Marakech is very tourist-friendly, with something like 80% of its revenue based on this, and we never felt unsafe.",2025-06-05T14:16:05Z,2025-06-05T14:16:05Z,0,True,,2026-05-07T02:02:05.228811
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgwenC8KdOftSAenlC94AaABAg.ACdy-O7b-QmACdyirKRdIP,UgwenC8KdOftSAenlC94AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Thanks for watching! We have had good success with Airbnb experiences (we aren't affiliated in any way and make no money by recommending them). Our guide was a little bit corny, but he gave us good insights and overall was a great guide. Here's a link to the experience—Colourful Tour of Marrakesh: https://www.airbnb.com/experiences/604421 —Judy",2024-12-29T22:32:49Z,2024-12-29T22:32:49Z,0,True,,2026-05-07T02:02:05.527133
