Tourism,hBQ6ObjF3W8,UgwdLklTiSCnLk9Pz-14AaABAg,,@dantimbreza6715,"The signs are already popping up here in Reno.  If you're into slots and electronic games its not that bad.  But, the table games minimum limits have gone up at the bigger casinos 2x to 5x.  I was used to $5 table games just to play and have fun but now $10/$15/$25 minimum bets are the norm downtown except for The CalNeva which (though a bit worn) have mostly stayed with the lower limits.  Outside of downtown, the GSR, PM, Nug, and Atl have also upped the table minimums, which is pushing locals (myself included) toward the smaller casinos in order to stretch my play time.  I hope that the big casino execs look at the non-convention/events days along with midweek traffic and see the drop in local foot traffic before its too late.",2026-05-06T18:52:49Z,2026-05-06T18:52:49Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-07T02:02:50.375332
