Tourism,hBQ6ObjF3W8,UgzHxjSeE1E9Y__67uB4AaABAg,,@jtjr26,"The problem is for decades the casinos were run by 'Casino' people. At some point the wall street types took over and started treating Vegas casinos like any other business. Streamlining policies, reducing staff and extracting as much money as possible with little regard to the health of the business or the city as a whole. Then the shift to more luxury at the expense of the average person happened. We are seeing the result of that in real time. The casino executives will not change until the lesson is harsh enough that they are forced to change. Also you can be sure that those same executives will do the same to Reno and any other small casino town if they can get away with it.",2026-05-06T17:50:37Z,2026-05-06T17:50:37Z,3,False,0.0,2026-05-07T02:02:50.375367
Tourism,hBQ6ObjF3W8,UgwrfqAkjCI23P7dcQR4AaABAg,,@dennisminer7436,"I know of about 10 Indian Casinos in Northern California and at least 3/4 of them are adding on new construction of hotel rooms. They are growing and compete directing with both Vegas and Reno for the gambling crowd. Why drive I-80 and risk a speeding ticket, heavy traffic in summer, or have to carrying snow chains in winter, when you can go much closer to home without any of that? What is the better bet? Answer: Local Indian casino. That's a Jackpot! They are not trying to squeeze the gamblers because there is too much competition with each other.",2026-05-06T17:08:38Z,2026-05-06T17:08:38Z,1,False,0.0,2026-05-07T02:02:50.375370
