Tourism,hBQ6ObjF3W8,Ugzcy5W-FD8r7oZlRvt4AaABAg,,@tkell31,"Just got back from Vegas.  Place was packed.   I gamble enough to get most things compd, but even that is getting insane as drink prices for things like an old fashioned are starting to exceed the $25/drink comp limit I get from Caesars.  Been thinking about giving Reno a shot.  And you can see in the video you are giving up some of the glitz, but without that glitz casinos can afford to operate with lower profit margins...giving the customer a better value in exchange for things most people dont care about in the first place.  Also in the video you can tell Reno is making better use of the space...they dont have huge areas meant to wow people and the higher percentage of square feet generating income the better deal you can give the customer.",2026-05-05T20:15:41Z,2026-05-05T20:15:41Z,8,False,0.0,2026-05-07T02:02:50.375474
