Tourism,wFZyNQAIcdE,UgyPH_7xRoYeOSpOz5N4AaABAg,,@rickymcc8624,"For sure just about anywhere can feel like ""hell on Earth"" if you choose to go unprepared, in high season, without doing proper research first and managing your expectations.

I have seen and enjoyed many of these, but season and time of day matters hugely.

IMO it's best to avoid anywhere when a massive cruise ship docks and a sunami of tourists wash inland.

So my top tips.
1) Do lots of research before travelling. Read Trip advisor reviews and if possible advice from friends who might have already been to place X.

2) Set realistic expectations, based on your research.

3) Ideally travel in the 'quieter' season. Get up and out at first light 5, 6 or 7am to have a real chance of missing the crowds.",2026-05-02T20:11:40Z,2026-05-02T20:11:40Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-07T02:02:54.754125
