Tourisme,tQG5jBBGn2Q,UgwQ3fXuYAZlQqmFimp4AaABAg,,@flowerwishes9936,"Before I say anything I’d like to say that when you live in SA, this is reality. This is what your life is and this is your normal. There are still incredible people, an incredible culture, a lot of really beautiful places, and it’s a country that’s been let down by the people in charge. This country has heart and it’s a shame that others will never get to see that. 

I moved from SA to the US about 5 years ago and despite having seen it in the movies, as we were driving to our airbnb from the airport, I looked at the house with no walls and a direct line straight to the front door and felt this sheer sense of unsafety. I knew in my head that this is what it's like here because I've seen it in media but actually seeing it didn't make sense to me. 
Also, my great aunt and uncle, both boardering on 80 years old,  were tied up by armed robbers in their home a couple years ago and have only just gotten to move out of their place because the housing market is so terrible.",2026-05-07T01:28:53Z,2026-05-07T01:47:57Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-07T02:04:07.689892
